This paper is primarily focused on face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also discusses adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and evolutionary algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses real-world face recognition systems, which could potentially fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
